`setw -g mouse off`  => give you back the mouse based copy and paste.  

→ but then we lose the ability to scroll the screen.
https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/312261/tmux-mouse-scrolling-without-altering-copy-paste


just do ctrl+b , [.   Then you can use page-up and page-down key. 
To exit, simply type ‘q’
⇒ this is basically a vi mode command!
=> to search, simply hit '/' key. press 'n' to jump to next searched result.  
=> Right hand top corner will show the number of result found.
⇒ you can't do with mouse.. but it is good the less you use mouse and more with keyboard. 
